A Matric learner gave birth during
her examination on Friday at a high school in Tsakane, Ekurhuleni, Gauteng
Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi announced in a post on Twitter. It is unclear at this stage which school the pupil attends at
this stage as well as the circumstances surrounding the ordeal. He also announced that a matriculant died during a robbery at
home. Learners were writing Mathematics P1, Mathematical Literacy P1
and Technical Mathematics P1, according the National Senior Certificate
timetable. Gauteng Department of Education Spokesperson, Steve Mabona was
not immediately available for comment. SOURCE: NEWS24